article.headline: Jackson State 74, Prairie View A&M 62
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas (AP) -- Trey Johnson scored 30 points to lead Jackson State to a 74-62 victory over Prairie View A&M on Monday. Johnson hit 9-of-17 from the field and 12-of-14 from the free-throw line. He was the only player in double figures for the Tigers (11-8, 5-1 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Dominique Sharpe and Brian Ezeh each scored 14 points for Prairie View (2-15, 0-5). Andy Genao added 10. Jackson State led 38-33 at the half. The Tigers shot 46 percent from the field to 41 percent for Prairie View.
